From a9d47234c0f722f1a751e37d31ed4e20f32bba1e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Josh Law <objecting@objecting.org>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 19:57:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] lib/logic_iomem: add bounds check to prevent overlapping
 mappings

In ioremap(), the logic IO memory framework computes the internal offset for the requested mapping but fails to verify whether offs + size fits within the internal MAX_AREA_SIZE (16MB). If an emulated device requests a mapping that crosses this boundary, subsequent accesses to the end of the mapping will overflow the address space and be routed to the wrong logic device operations structure.

Add a bounds check to ensure offs + size does not exceed MAX_AREA_SIZE, preventing out-of-bounds cross-device routing.

Signed-off-by: Josh Law <objecting@objecting.org>
---
 lib/logic_iomem.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/lib/logic_iomem.c b/lib/logic_iomem.c
index 42a571d05670..f3012998b4d1 100644
--- a/lib/logic_iomem.c
+++ b/lib/logic_iomem.c
@@ -116,6 +116,11 @@ void __iomem *ioremap(phys_addr_t offset, size_t size)
 			break;
 		}
 
+		if (WARN_ON(offs + size > MAX_AREA_SIZE)) {
+			mapped_areas[i].ops = NULL;
+			break;
+		}
+
 		if (WARN_ON(!mapped_areas[i].ops)) {
 			mapped_areas[i].ops = NULL;
 			break;
-- 
2.34.1

